        body: 'A vibration lure\'s thin body catches water and produces a tight, rapid shimmy. Its greatest advantages are casting distance and search coverage. Most models weigh 14-21g, enabling long casts on baitcasting tackle. They begin vibrating the instant you start the retrieve, making operation effortless. By varying retrieve speed, you can cover every depth from bottom to surface. They also handle advanced techniques like lift-and-fall and bottom bumping. The main drawback is snag susceptibility, but learning to pop the rod tip the moment you feel bottom contact will keep hang-ups to a minimum.',
